Still not quite enough. If you have paths `/a/b/c` and `/a/b/cd`, then the second starts with the first but is not an actual parent directory. There's [`os.path.commonpath()`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/os.path.html#os.path.commonpath), but that was only added in Py3.5.  For Py2.7, we'd then need a fallback. However, you could simply append `os.sep` to `src_base_dir` to make the comparison safer.
